{
  "stem": "13313.5",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The fact that even though, we have this, this, this uproar about this, this, this Latvian S.S killer living peacefully as a refugee in, in, in an apartment building where a lot of Holocaust survivors live who are totally disturbed.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "When I see all that and see what's going with Israel, and, and Islamic antisemitism, and the Farrakhans and all this, I-- and also, the fact that there is not enough outrage based on what happened in World War II to make this like, unthinkable, impossible, then I get very disturbed.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I-- and, and, and I get very, very cynical.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It has to do-- it has to do with the lack of-- lack-- the indifference has to do-- this indifference, this lack of awareness, lack of knowledge, and lack of care, by a lot of Jewish people as well, not only by non-Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "For example, as I mentioned, there was this episode where Chaim Herzog, President of Israel, visited Canada and addressed an audience at the Sheraton Hotel, just on Queen Street at Nathan Phillips Square.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "When I heard, we went there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We parked our car underneath and went to attend.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "In the middle of his speech, news filtered in that there were demonstrations outside.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And he said, there are some-- there's some Palestinians demonstrating with all kinds of flags and, and, and symbols and slogans.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And he said, they'll probably-- the the reporters, he said, would probably give more importance to that news than to what I have to say.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I was very curious.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So my wife and I stepped outside to see what was going on.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the scene was that across from the hotel, cordoned off, because there were police, was this group.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Maybe a couple hundred Palestinians with Palestinian flags.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
